<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n33328h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n33" href="#n33328h">N33 (VI.B.4)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n33all.htm#n33328h"> 328(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> S. Josaphus / Cyril &amp; Method</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Il ne perd point une occasion d&apos;exalter les gloires d&apos;Orient: ce sont les f&ecirc;tes centenaires <mark>de saint Josaphat, des saints Cyrille et M&eacute;thode</mark>. <small> Ren&eacute; Fontanelle. <a name="PIUS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#PIUS"><cite title="source">Sa Saintet&eacute; Pie XI</cite></a> (n.d.) 42</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Josaphat Kuncevyc (1580-1623) was a saint and martyr. Saints Cyril and Methodius (9th century) were the apostles of the Slavs. They learnt the Slavonic tongue, invented an alphabet, and translated the Gospel and liturgical books into Slavonic.</mm> </dd></dl>
